\p
\v 1 \add ≈During the reign\add* of King Ahaz¦285460 (son of Yotam, son of Uzziyah) in¦285459 Yehudah¦285468 \add (Judah)\add*, King Retsin¦285470 from Aram¦285473 and King Pekah¦285474 (son of Remaliah¦285477) from Yisrael¦285480, went¦285469 up to Yerushalem¦285481 \add ≈attack¦285486\add* it, but¦285458 they \add ≈weren't able to conquer\add* it.\x + \xo 7:1: \xt 2Ki 16:5; 2Ch 28:5-6.\x*
\v 2 Tt was reported¦285489 to David's¦285491 \add ≈descendants\add* that Aram¦285494 \add (Syria¦285494)\add* stands by with Efrayim¦285497, and \add @the king\add* and the people¦285501 trembled just like the trees¦285503 in the forest¦285505 shaking in the wind¦285508.
