\v 13 Then¦285661 \add @Yeshayah\add* said¦285661, “\add ≈You descendants\add* of David¦285666 \add ≈need to listen¦285662\add*. \add ≈It's bad enough¦285667 that you're wearing out the people¦285670, but¦285661 why are you also annoying\add* my god¦285676?
\v 14 \add ≈Because of that\add*, my master¦285680 will \add ≈take the initiative himself to choose\add* a sign¦285683: listen, a young¦285685, virgin woman¦285685\f + \fr 7:14 \ft See https://textandcanon.org/does-isaiah-predict-the-virgin-birth.\f* will \add ≈become pregnant¦285686\add* and give¦285679 birth to a son, and will name¦285690 him ‘Immanuel¦285691’ \add (which means ‘God is with us’.)\add*.\x + \xo 7:14: \xt Mat 1:23.\x*
\v 15 He'll know how to refuse evil¦285699 and do good¦285701 \add ≈by the time¦285697 that he¦285696 can\add* eat¦285696 yoghurt and honey¦285695.
\v 16 \add ≈However,\add* before¦285704 the child \add ≈is old enough to do that\add*, the \add ≈countries\add* of the two¦285717 kings¦285718 that you're¦285714 afraid of, will become deserted.
