\v 17 \add But¦285723 instead,\add* Yahweh¦285721 will bring¦285720 the Assyrian king¦285742 to \add attack\add* you¦285722 and your¦285725 people¦285725, and \add ≈David's dynasty will be under¦285739 it's greatest stress\add* since¦285735 Efrayim \add (Yisrael)\add* broke away from Yehudah¦285740 \add (Judah)\add*.”
\p
\v 18 \add ≈When that happens,\add* Yahweh¦285751 will whistle¦285750 for a fly that's in Egypt's¦285756 distant streams, and for a bee that's in Assyria¦285760.
\v 19 They'll all come¦285762 and settle¦285763 down in deserted valleys and cracks in the rocks¦285768, and in all the thornbushes¦285770 and watering¦285772 holes¦285772.
\p
\v 20 \add ≈At that time,\add* my master¦285777 will use a hired¦285779 razor¦285778 from beyond¦285780 the \add ≈Euphrates\add* to shave¦285776 the head¦285786 and legs of the Assyrian king¦285782, and to remove his beard¦285793.
