\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh¦285878 told me, “Get yourself¦285882 a large¦285884, \add stone\add* tablet¦285883 and inscribe \add the name\add* ‘Maher-Shalal-Hash-Baz’ \add (which means ‘Quickly plunder and grab the loot’)\add* on¦285887 it,
\v 2 and I'll¦285894 get my reliable¦285897 witnesses¦285896 to attest for me: the priest¦285900 Uriyah, and Yeverekyah's son Zekaryah.
\p
\v 3 Then¦285907 I \add ≈slept with\add* \add my wife\add*, the prophetess¦285910, and she got pregnant¦285911 and \add in due course,\add* gave¦285912 birth¦285912 to a son. Yahweh¦285915 told me, “Name him Maher-Shalal-Hash-Baz¦285922,
\v 4 because before¦285925 he's old enough to call out ‘papa’ or ‘mama’, the riches from Damascus¦285936 and the plunder¦285938 from Shomron¦285939 \add (Samaria¦285939)\add* will \add all\add* be taken \add ≈to be presented to\add* the Assyrian¦285942 king¦285941.
