\v 13 Then¦294251 the \add ≈negotiator\add* stood¦294251 \add and looked up\add*, and \add ≈shouted in Hebrew\add*, “Listen to this message from the great Assyrian king.
\v 14 The king says not to let \add your king\add* Hezkiyah deceive¦294275 you all, because¦294278 he won't¦294273 be able to save you.
\v 15 Don't¦294285 let \add *him\add* make¦294287 you \add ≈rely on\add* Yahweh by telling you all that Yahweh will rescue¦294294 you, and¦294285 that this city¦294299 won't¦294285 be \add ≈captured by\add* the Assyrian king¦294302.
\v 16 \add No,\add* don't¦294305 listen¦294307 to Hezkiyah, because¦294312 the Assyrian king¦294315 says¦294314 that \add ≈if you all surrender and come¦294321 out here, you'll be allowed to continue to harvest\add* your own grapevines and fig¦294328 trees, and everyone will be able to drink¦294329 the water¦294331 from their own wells
\v 17 until I come and take you to a land like your own \add that has\add* grain¦294345 and new wine—a land with bread¦294348 and vineyards¦294349.
\p
\v 18 “\add ≈Don't let\add* Hezkiyah mislead¦294353 you all by saying that Yahweh¦294357 will rescue¦294358 you. Did the gods¦294360 of \add any other\add* nations¦294361 saved them from the Assyrian king's \add ≈power\add*?
\v 19 Where were Hamat¦294372 and Arpad's¦294373 gods? Where were Sefarvayim's gods? \add ≈Did any gods\add* save Shomron¦294382 \add (Samaria¦294382)\add* from my \add ≈power\add*?
\v 20 From all those¦294391 \add ≈regions¦294396\add*, which¦294391 of their¦294396 gods¦294388 saved them from my \add ≈power\add*, \add so what makes you all think that¦294391\add* Yahweh¦294401 will save Yerushalem¦294404 from \add *me\add*.”
\p
\v 21 \add ≈But¦294407\add* \add @those on the wall\add* kept¦294407 silent¦294407 and¦294407 didn't¦294408 answer¦294420 him¦294420, because¦294413 King¦294416 \add Hezkiyah\add* had ordered them not to respond.
