\v 3 and they told him, “\add King\add* Hezkiyah says that \add ≈today\add* is a day of distress¦294500 and rebuke¦294501 and disgrace, \add ≈like when children¦294507 go to their mother who's about to deliver her baby\add* \add ≈but¦294493 she doesn't have the strength¦294511 to\add* give birth¦294513.
\v 4 Perhaps your god Yahweh heard the messages from \add ≈the negotiator\add* who was sent by his master¦294531, the Assyrian king, to defy the living¦294534 god. \add ≡Perhaps\add* \add @Yahweh\add* will rebuke¦294535 \add him for\add* the words that¦294537 Yahweh heard. \add ≈So send\add* up a prayer¦294542 for the remnant¦294544 \add ≈of us here\add*.”
