\v 38 \add One day\add* he was worshipping in the \add ≈temple\add* of his god¦295125 Nisrok, and his sons¦295128 Adrammelek and Sharetser \add ≈ran a sword¦295130 through him before\add* escaping¦295132 to the Ararat¦295134 \add ≈region¦295133\add*, and his son Esar-Haddon \add ≈replaced him as king¦295135\add*.
