\p
\v 1 \add ≈Then a time¦295143 came when\add* \add King\add* Hezkiyah became¦295145 \add ≈critically ill\add*, and the prophet¦295154 Yeshayah (\add Isaiah¦295150\add*, Amots' son) went¦295148 to him and told him, “Yahweh¦295160 says \add ≈that you should put all your affairs into order, because¦295163 you won't¦295166 recover—your time is up\add*.”
