\v 6 and will rescue¦295244 \add both\add* him and \add @Yerushalem\add* from the Assyrian king. \add @Yahweh\add* will defend¦295248 this city
\v 7 and¦295254 this will be the sign¦295257 from \add *him\add* that¦295267 \add *he\add* will do¦295261 what he's said,
\v 8 ‘Look, I will turn¦295271 the shadow on the steps \add built by King\add* Ahaz¦295279, back ten steps.’ ” So the sun's shadow went¦295284 back \add up\add* ten steps that¦295276 it had gone down.
\s2 Hezkiyah's poem of praise
