\p
\v 9 Yehudah's¦295297 King¦295295 Hezkiyah¦295294 \add ≈wrote this\add* \add poem\add* \add ≈after he'd recovered\add* from his sickness¦295300:
\q1
\v 10 I said¦295303, “I'll go¦295306 through the gates¦295307 \add ≈to the grave\add* in the \add ≈prime\add* of my life,
\q1 ≈I'll miss out on the remainder¦295310 of my years¦295311.”
\q1
\v 11 I said, “I won't¦295314 see Yah in the land¦295319 of the living.
\q1 ≈I'll¦295316 no longer look at humankind¦295324 \add ≈but rather\add* those who've ceased living.”
\q1
\v 12 \add ≈The body that I live in\add* has been pulled¦295332 up and¦295333 removed¦295333 from \add over\add* me like a shepherd's¦295336 tent¦295335.
\q1 ≈I've¦295337 rolled¦295337 my¦295346 life¦295339 up like a weaver¦295338 cutting me off from the loom.
