\q1
\v 13 I lie down\f + \fr 38:13 \ft The Hebrew could be read: \fqa I cried out \ft or \fq I lie down\ft .\f* until the morning¦295351.
\q1 He breaks¦295354 all my¦295362 bones¦295357 like a lion¦295352 \add would\add*.
\q1 From day¦295358 until night¦295361, you¦295362 make¦295362 an end¦295362 of me.
\q1
\v 14 I chirp¦295367 like a swallow¦295364 and moan like a dove¦295369.
\q1 My eyes¦295371 \add ?≈feel weak from looking upwards\add*.
\q1 I'm oppressed¦295374, my master¦295373, \add ≈help me out\add*.
